content:
Is there a practical way to create a PDF from a list of images files using Python? In Perl, I know a module (PDF::FromImage) that allows me to create a PDF in just 3 lines of code:

```perl
use PDF::FromImage;
...
my $pdf = PDF::FromImage->new;
$pdf->load_images(@allPagesDir);
$pdf->write_file($bookName . '.pdf');
```
I am looking for something similar in Python. I am aware of the pyPdf module, but I prefer something simpler.
